</h3><h3></h3><p><a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/alienware-announces-a-new-look-aurora-r16-desktop-070153737.html"><ins>Alienware 推出全新外观的 Aurora R16 台式机</ins></a></p><p><a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/xbox-gamers-can-now-stream-directly-to-discord-150045129.html"><ins>Xbox 玩家现在可以直接串流至 Discord</ins></a></p><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/meta-releases-an-open-source-ai-kit-that-creates-audio-from-text-prompts-152026368.html"><ins>Meta 发布了一个开源 AI 套件，可以根据文本提示创建音频</ins></a></p><p><a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/googles-chrome-updates-bring-improved-search-to-mobile-and-simpler-desktop-downloads-160003908.html"><ins>谷歌的 Chrome 更新改进了移动搜索并简化了桌面下载</ins></a></p><p><a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/nintendo-brings-mario-kart-8-and-splatoon-for-wii-u-back-online-august-3rd-165434085.html"><ins>任天堂将《马里奥赛车 8》和《喷射战士》Wii U 版于 8 月 3 日重新上线</ins></a></p><p><a data-i13n="cpos:8;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/bytedance-sued-for-allegedly-collecting-biometric-data-without-consent-172411924.html"><ins>字节跳动因涉嫌未经同意收集生物识别数据而被起诉</ins></a></p><p><a data-i13n="cpos:9;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/the-sonos-move-2-will-reportedly-offer-stereo-audio-and-24-hour-battery-life-181950125.html"><ins>据报道，Sonos Move 2 将提供立体声音频和 24 小时电池续航时间</ins></a></p><p><a data-i13n="cpos:10;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/the-irs-wants-to-phase-out-most-irl-tax-documents-by-2025-192105265.html"><ins>IRS 希望到 2025 年逐步淘汰大部分 IRL 税务文件</ins></a></p><p><a data-i13n="cpos:11;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/ai-assisted-cancer-screening-could-cut-radiologist-workloads-in-half-193427969.html"><ins>人工智能辅助癌症筛查可以将放射科医生的工作量减少一半</ins></a></p><h2><a data-i13n="cpos:12;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/china-considers-limiting-kids-smartphone-time-to-two-hours-per-day-134708060.html"><ins>中国考虑将儿童使用智能手机的时间限制为每天两小时</ins></a></h2><h3>这是减少智能手机成瘾的另一项举措。</h3><p></p><p>中国国家互联网信息办公室 (CAC) 提出的立法草案<a data-i13n="cpos:13;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/china-considers-limiting-kids-smartphone-time-to-two-hours-per-day-134708060.html"><ins>将进一步限制 18 岁以下的手机使用</ins></a>。这是该国遏制智能手机成瘾努力的一部分，该国已经限制了孩子每周玩游戏的时间。该提案将使 16 岁至 18 岁的孩子每天使用两个小时，而 8 岁到 15 岁的孩子每天使用一个小时——对于 8 岁以下的孩子来说运气不好，他们每天只能使用 40 分钟，而且还限制了使用时间。他们可以访问。</p><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:14;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/china-considers-limiting-kids-smartphone-time-to-two-hours-per-day-134708060.html"><strong><ins>继续阅读。</ins></strong></a></p><h2> <a data-i13n="cpos:15;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/canons-new-security-focused-spad-camera-can-capture-color-video-in-complete-darkness-095516159.html"><ins>佳能全新专注于安全的 SPAD 相机可在完全黑暗的环境中捕捉彩色视频</ins></a></h2><h3>它使用 SPAD（单光子雪崩二极管）传感器。</h3> <a href="https://www.engadget.com/canons-new-security-focused-spad-camera-can-capture-color-video-in-complete-darkness-095516159.html"><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-08/f239be90-31e0-11ee-bffe-f22ed11b1c45" style="height:407px;width:625px;" alt="佳能新型 MS-500 SPAD 摄像机的宣传图片，专为在超低光照条件下拍摄彩色视频而设计。" data-uuid="0de2c488-df58-328d-ba2b-37eede034931"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">佳能</div></figure></a><p>如果您有 25,000 美元并且对夜间摄影充满热情，那么佳能的新款<a data-i13n="cpos:16;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/canons-new-security-focused-spad-camera-can-capture-color-video-in-complete-darkness-095516159.html"><ins>MS-500 就是您的最佳选择</ins></a>。该公司承诺，这款相机可以在低至 0.001 勒克斯的光线下拍摄清晰的彩色视频，对于我们这些不懂技术的人来说，<em>这种光线实在是太暗了。</em>这个特殊的装置被设计为高安全设施的安全摄像头，但随着技术的成熟，能够实现夜间功能的新型传感器肯定会出现在其他硬件中。</p><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:17;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/canons-new-security-focused-spad-camera-can-capture-color-video-in-complete-darkness-095516159.html"><strong><ins>继续阅读。</ins></strong></a></p><h2> <a data-i13n="cpos:18;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/kickstarter-projects-will-soon-have-to-disclose-any-ai-use-145100394.html"><ins>Kickstarter 项目很快将不得不披露任何人工智能的使用</ins></a></h2><h3>该平台正在针对自动抄袭的风险采取立场。</h3><p></p><p> 8 月 29 日或之后提交的 Kickstarter 项目必须<a data-i13n="cpos:19;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/kickstarter-projects-will-soon-have-to-disclose-any-ai-use-145100394.html"><ins>披露是否使用了人工智能</ins></a>。该平台的信任和安全负责人表示，众筹网站希望确保创作者不会靠被盗作品赚钱。<em>使用</em>人工智能的创作者还必须声明他们拥有使用这些输出的适当信用和许可。</p><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:20;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/kickstarter-projects-will-soon-have-to-disclose-any-ai-use-145100394.html"><strong><ins>继续阅读。</ins></strong></a></p><h2> <a data-i13n="cpos:21;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/ibm-and-nasa-teamed-up-to-build-the-gpt-of-earth-sciences-040116377.html"><ins>IBM 与 NASA 联手打造地球科学 GPT</ins></a></h2><h3>开源气候模型将利用美国宇航局数百万兆字节的数据。</h3><p></p><p>到 2024 年，NASA 预计仅通过地球科学实验就能产生 25 万 TB 的数据。处理如此大量的信息是不可能的，因此该机构向 IBM 和 HuggingFace 寻求帮助。三人构建了一个<a data-i13n="cpos:22;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/ibm-and-nasa-teamed-up-to-build-the-gpt-of-earth-sciences-040116377.html"><ins>开源基础模型</ins></a>，该模型将构成人工智能的支柱，用于跟踪森林砍伐、预测农作物产量和记录温室气体排放。</p><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:23;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/ibm-and-nasa-teamed-up-to-build-the-gpt-of-earth-sciences-040116377.html"><strong><ins>继续阅读。</ins></strong></a></p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><h2> <a data-i13n="cpos:24;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/x-blue-subscribers-can-now-hide-their-checkmarks-110229094.html"><ins>X Blue 订阅者现在可以隐藏他们的耻辱和复选标记</ins></a></h2><h3>任务完成？</h3><p></p><p>想象一下，您对一种防欺诈工具如此着迷，以至于花费了 440 亿美元来破坏它的使用。现在想象一下，其他人对这个工具非常着迷，以至于他们每月花费 8 美元来破坏它的使用。如果花了这么多时间、金钱和精力来获得他们认为是荣誉徽章的东西，突然意识到这根本不是荣誉徽章，那将是多么黑暗可笑的事情。如果他们<a data-i13n="cpos:25;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/x-blue-subscribers-can-now-hide-their-checkmarks-110229094.html"><ins>都选择隐藏他们渴望已久的徽章</ins></a>，你可能会笑，不是吗？你不会吗？</p><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:26;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/x-blue-subscribers-can-now-hide-their-checkmarks-110229094.html"><strong><ins>继续阅读。</ins></strong></a></p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><h2> <a data-i13n="cpos:27;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/elon-musk-says-hell-ask-tim-cook-to-lower-app-store-fees-for-x-subscriptions-223952210.html"><ins>埃隆·马斯克表示，他将要求蒂姆·库克降低 App Store 的 X 订阅费用</ins></a></h2><h3>埃隆能在几乎其他人都失败的地方（检查笔记）取得成功吗？</h3><p></p><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:28;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/elon-musk-says-hell-ask-tim-cook-to-lower-app-store-fees-for-x-subscriptions-223952210.html"><ins>祝</ins></a>你好运，伙计。</p><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:29;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/elon-musk-says-hell-ask-tim-cook-to-lower-app-store-fees-for-x-subscriptions-223952210.html"><strong><ins>继续阅读</ins></strong></a><strong>。</strong></p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/the-morning-after-are-samsungs-folding-screens-sturdy-enough-111557475.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/the-morning-after-are-samsungs-folding-screens-sturdy-enough-111557475.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 02558786-6a6f-4016-b79c-a34e1ffd94a0</guid><dc:creator>丹尼尔·库珀</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Thu, 03 Aug 2023 11:15:57 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1691058031</ingested><modified> 2023-08-03T10:20:43+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Daniel Cooper]]></category><media:content height="1200" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-08/922752b0-31e0-11ee-bff2-68ec487a6d05" width="2000"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="1200" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-08/922752b0-31e0-11ee-bff2-68ec487a6d05" width="2000"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Photo by Sam Rutherford / Engadget]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[Close-up image of Sam Rutherford's Z Fold 4 on a table, visibly showing the display crease.]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Samsung Z Fold 4 Display]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[X sued by AFP over not discussing payments for news content]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>埃隆·马斯克 (Elon Musk) 和 X（前身为 Twitter）网站面临<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/elon-musk-is-taking-his-sec-fight-to-the-supreme-court-161255874.html">更多法律麻烦</a>。 <a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.afp.com/en/agency/press-releases-newsletter/afp-takes-legal-action-against-twitter-enforce-news-agencies-and-publishers-neighbouring-rights">法新社 (AFP) 起诉 X</a>未参与有关向法国出版商付款以换取其文章出现在该平台上的讨论。 2019年， <a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/france-google-scraping-stories-snippets-104038211.html">法国通过了邻接权立法</a>，将版权法延伸至新闻出版商制作的内容，例如文本和视频，有效期为发布后两年。法律要求任何分享该作品的网站必须与出版商协商报酬，而不是在不向创作者提供补偿的情况下分享该作品。 </p><div id="c3e2ffbe71714056ba64313abc4be84d"><blockquote class="twitter-tweet"><p lang="en" dir="ltr">这很奇怪。他们希望我们向*他们*支付他们网站的流量费用，他们可以在其中赚取广告收入，而我们却没有！？</p> — 埃隆·马斯克 (@elonmusk) <a href="https://twitter.com/elonmusk/status/1686927028644179968?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">2023 年 8 月 3 日</a></blockquote></div><p>法新社在其新闻稿中表示，它“对 Twitter（最近更名为“X”）明确拒绝就新闻界实施邻接权进行讨论表示担忧。设立这些权利是为了使新闻能够传播机构和出版商将通过数字平台获得报酬，这些平台保留了新闻内容分发所产生的大部分货币价值。”</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p> X并不是法新社反对的第一家科技公司。 2020 年，法国竞争主管机构命令谷歌与出版商进行谈判，虽然它<a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/google-agreement-french-publishers-content-100220969.html">在 2021 年初达成协议</a>，但该<a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/france-google-antitrust-fine-news-publishers-143000932.html">公司在当年晚些时候因未达成公平协议而被罚款 5 亿欧元</a>（5.46 亿美元）。在这种情况下，部分争论是谷歌拥有 90% 的搜索市场，如果没有达成公平的协议，他们就可能滥用权力。 Twitter 在互联网这一领域的影响力远没有那么强大，因此我们必须拭目以待，看看它是否会面临同样的战斗。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/x-sued-by-afp-over-not-discussing- payments-for-news-content-105501199.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/x-sued-by-afp-over-not-discussing-payments-for-news-content-105501199.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 0d12fdae-fc36-4a09-a98a-3e8abbde6ae2</guid><dc:creator>萨拉·菲尔丁</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Thu, 03 Aug 2023 10:55:01 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1691059386</ingested><modified> 2023-08-03T10:43:11+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Finance Trading]]></category><category><![CDATA[Media]]></category><category><![CDATA[Company Legal & Law Matters]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Sarah Fielding]]></category><media:content height="2269" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2021-07/b5154ca0-e3e5-11eb-a2bf-cfba746a4223" width="3400"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="2269" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2021-07/b5154ca0-e3e5-11eb-a2bf-cfba746a4223" width="3400"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[FRED DUFOUR via Getty Images]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[A copy of the newspaper "L'opinion" is pictured in a newsstand on May 15, 2013 in Paris. The newspaper, also available online, was released on May 15, 2013 in France. AFP PHOTO/FRED DUFOUR        (Photo credit should read FRED DUFOUR/AFP via Getty Images)]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[FRANCE-MEDIA-INTERNET]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Meta report admits its Ray-Ban Stories smart glasses aren't getting much face time]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>无论科技公司的某些产品取得了多大的成功，至少有一款设备在推出后总是无法达到预期。亚马逊在其<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/2014-07-22-amazon-fire-phone-review.html">迅速停产的 Fire 手机</a>中经历了这一点，而 Meta 则在从<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/how-meta-flunked-its-first-year-as-a-metaverse-company-150049067.html">对 Metaverse 不感兴趣</a>到据报道的<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/facebook-ray-ban-stories-smart-glasses-ar-160006477.html">Ray-Ban Stories</a>智能太阳镜等各个方面都看到了这一点。根据<a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:The Wall Street Journal;elmt:;cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=2f007401-3eaa-4237-b69b-54ccbe125502&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=The+Wall+Street+Journal&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAdf64c6xA4znB45aa1OPuGyojss-y70hQYri-4sQdPiy&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Farticles%2Fmetas-ray-ban-smart-glasses-fail-to-catch-on-31f6ba4e%3Fmod%3De2twd" class="rapid-with-clickid"><em>《华尔街日报》</em>查看的一份内部 Meta 文件，</a>拥有 Ray-Ban Stories 的人中只有不到 10% 经常使用该产品。</p><p>雷朋 (Ray-Ban) 眼镜在 2021 年 9 月推出至 2023 年 2 月（Meta 进行报告时）期间售出约 30 万副。当时，每月只有 27,000 名活跃用户，该公司指出存在连接不良和电池寿命问题等问题。是的，这些人已经购买了太阳镜，所以这对公司来说是好事，但低保留率并不能完全增强对持续销售的信心。雷朋 (Ray-Ban) 合作伙伴关系所属的<a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/meta-q3-2022-earnings-211903277.html">Meta 现实实验室部门</a>也表现不佳，2023 年上半年亏损近 800 万美元。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>然而，Meta 计划在秋季或春季发布新一代 Ray-Ban Stories。显然，这款新眼镜的电池寿命和摄像头将得到改善，并且比目前的三种太阳镜型号有更多的选择。虽然第一代的售价为 299 美元，但目前还没有关于下一代<a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/facebook-ray-ban-stories-hands-on-160048150.html">Ray-Ban Stories</a>的定价的消息。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/meta-memo-admits-its-ray-ban-stories-smart-glasses-arent-getting-much-face-time-094549256.html?src =rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/meta-memo-admits-its-ray-ban-stories-smart-glasses-arent-getting-much-face-time-094549256.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> d8cc3c5a-e871-43e0-87c7-446fa8b0726a</guid><dc:creator>萨拉·菲尔丁</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Thu, 03 Aug 2023 09:45:49 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1691058731</ingested><modified> 2023-08-03T10:32:13+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Sarah Fielding]]></category><media:content height="984" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-03/b1159890-b7f0-11ed-adfe-70ded4543024" width="1750"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="984" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-03/b1159890-b7f0-11ed-adfe-70ded4543024" width="1750"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Meta]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[A promo photo of a p